    "Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) encode input data into a latent space representation and subsequently reconstruct it, enabling the generation of new data points through latent space sampling.",
    "By manipulating values of latent variables, VAEs can interpolate and generate novel data points, diversifying/augmenting the dataset.",
    "VAEs have proven invaluable in bioinformatics for synthesizing genomic data and drug discovery for creating novel molecular structures, enhancing research and development efficiency.",
    "Samanta et al. (2020) presented NEVAE, a novel VAE specifically designed for generating novel molecular graphs.",
    "NEVAE innovates by providing spatial coordinates for atoms in generated molecules while ensuring specific desirable chemical properties."
